N:game-ci-cd-pipeline
D:Turn messy Unity or Unreal build/release automation into one bounded pipeline packet: setup plan, stage split, cache policy, preflight checklist, artifact/release hygiene, or CI-signal hardening. Use when a game team needs to design or repair GitHub Actions, Unity Build Automation, Jenkins, TeamCity, or similar CI for engine builds — especially when they mention flaky packaging, cache superstition, giant build-job blobs, slow cook / package cycles, artifact confusion, SDK/signing drift, or a manual game release process that should become reproducible. Route one red log first-pass diagnosis to `game-build-log-triage`.
G:game-development unity unreal ci-cd github-actions build-pipeline release-engineering

U[5]:
  Unity or Unreal teams setting up CI/CD from scratch without overengineering it
  Pipelines that are repeatedly flaky, slow, or opaque because workflow structure is weak
  Build, cook/package, cache, artifact, or release handoff issues that keep breaking trust
  Small studios still making demo/review/release builds manually
  Contractor or technical-lead audits that need a compact game-pipeline brief

S[7]{n,action,details}:
  1,Choose one primary packet type,Normalize the request into exactly one packet: pipeline-setup, stage-split, cache-policy, preflight-readiness, artifact-release, ci-signal-hardening, or route-to-log-triage.
  2,Gather the minimum credible evidence,Collect engine/version, CI surface, target platforms, repeated failure pattern, manual steps outside CI, and one failed job/log if relevant.
  3,Classify the primary blocker,Pick one primary blocker and at most one secondary blocker.
  4,Run the boundary check,Verify whether this is structural pipeline work or should route to `game-build-log-triage`.
  5,Build the packet brief,Return the exact Game CI/CD Brief with packet choice, evidence, blockers, recommended shape, route-outs, and one next artifact.
  6,Tailor the packet to the engine,Use Unity- or Unreal-specific guidance without bloating the front door.
  7,Ask for the smallest missing packet,Request only the missing inputs that change the decision.
